cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper focuses on the measurement and characterization of the Bitcoin peer-to-peer network, which involves network infrastructure, security, distributed computing, and cybersecurity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the usage patterns of the Bitcoin network, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The evaluation of the re-identification method could be considered as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
